        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/tampering",
          "message": {
            "text": "The Orchestrator's context window (system prompt, retrieved documents, tool results) can be tampered with by an attacker who controls any upstream data source \u2014 the Knowledge Base, the Inter-Agent Channel (aggregated results), or tool call responses from the MCP Tool Server. Injecting adversarial content into the context manipulates the Orchestrator's reasoning and outputs.",
            "markdown": "Validate the integrity of all context sources before injecting into the Orchestrator's context window. Apply content-level hashing to retrieved documents at KB read time. Treat tool results as untrusted input and apply output encoding before context injection."
          },
          "level": "error",
          "locations": [
