          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/denial-of-service",
          "message": {
            "text": "The Channel's message queue can be flooded by a compromised agent or a malfunctioning process, causing legitimate messages to be dropped, delayed, or rejected. Queue saturation disrupts coordination between Orchestrator and Specialist Agent.",
            "markdown": "Implement message queue depth limits and per-sender rate limits at the Channel layer. Apply backpressure mechanisms: when the queue approaches capacity, reject new messages from the sender with a rate-limit response. Monitor queue depth metrics and alert on sustained high-water-mark conditions."
          },
          "level": "error",
